![ Each "unit" of the mobile is a flower epoxied to a stem---the stem is the support
   and the flower hangs off one arm.
   Each "unit" integrates the stem with the object balancing off it.
   More "units" hang off the other arm.
](/images/mobile/flower-closeup.jpg)


![ Previously, my mobiles involved well-balanced "see-saws"---either simple bamboo
    skewers, or stylized metal supports, counterbalanced so that they were flat.
    This mobile takes advantage of wildly unbalanced supports.
    In its "balanced" configuration, the supports are almost vertical.
](/images/mobile/typical-mobile.jpg)



